<h1>Problem 1460 - 2023 INMO, P6 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Euclid has a tool called cyclos which allows him to do the following:</p>
<p><ul><li>Given three non-collinear marked points, draw the circle passing through them.</li><li>Given two marked points, draw the circle with them as endpoints of a diameter.</li><li>Mark any intersection points of two drawn circles or mark a new point on a drawn circle.</li></ul></p>
<p>Show that, given two marked points, Euclid can draw a circle centered at one of them and passing through the other, using only the cyclos.</p>
